>vegetarianism is just a carnist diet and it's less than marginally better than if you still ate flesh.
this is true for factory farming, but assuming you had access to farmers who treated animals ethically you could reasonably get dairy / eggs / honey while still treating animals with compassion. it's not like nature is a fairer mistress.
of course there are the environmental issues to consider which still make switching to being completely vegan the optimal choice
unfortunately the fact of the matter is that it's also just difficult for your average person to go vegan - pushing it as an "either / or" thing doesn't help anybody, imo. if someone gives up meat 3 days a week, that's still a lot less meat being eaten. my state gives out a metric shitton in food stamps and i still struggle to afford eating just vegetarian (switched to vegan in some regards e.g. all my sandwich stuff is vegan, but i unfortunately rely on easy meals bc my place is disgusting and cockroach infested and i don't want to leave raw ingredients out, and vegan easy meals are a barren, overpriced desert)
it's like the plastic straw thing. the problem isn't people using plastic straws, the problem is plastic straws being sold everywhere and alternatives being specialty goods you have to look for to find. most working class people are just trying to get by and can't afford to go out of their way to find ethical alternatives to everything they purchase - they go for what's available. which is why voting with your wallet will never be as effective as government regulation

>>29648439
>post-orchi
perfect

>try lower than 4mg EV every 5 days
unfortunately EV is the least suitable ester for lower levels as you'd have to inject so often to keep the peak low enough as the peak goes too high for longer injection cycles and so more likely to end up feeling bad mentally/getting hot flashes desu
You'd have to use EEn or EC for low lvls w/injections as it's stable levels throughout your entire normal length injection cycle to allow lh/fsh to go higher

Oral e could work at a low 2-3mg dose, and same with low dose transdermal, or low dose EEn/EC
For exact lvls it's tricky, but the best guide is puberty; u wanna avoid post-menses/ovulation levels and stick around pre-menses/early-puberty lvls which is honestly kinda low for minimum lvls (15).
so ideally, for us, that'd mean above menopause (above 30pg/mL) but below maximum e2 for early pre-menses puberty (85-100pg/mL e2, numbers vary across studies).
There is also another factor here with the igf-1 signaling pathway switching between a growth prone pathway at low early puberty levels and switching to a less growth prone pathway at higher/post-puberty levels so that probably has something to do with it too.

ofc u are encouraged to experiment, going a bit higher or w/e as theory is just theory, but basically u want stable low levels here; take also into consideration that at these low levels u need stable lvls to not feel like crap mentally as low dipping levels will make u feel bad. Tip tho, oral e2 is pretty stable after a few weeks due to building a reservoir of sulfated/etc estrogens and even at low doses.

Goal of the thread: Think of something you are grateful for. Feel free to share it with us, but no pressure!

Daily goals can be repeated. Remember to keep score, it can only go up!

>What is this thread for?
Getting better is hard, and sucks. A lot. It does not get easier doing it alone.
Share resources and experiences with combating depression, anxiety, personal issues, achieving or maintaining a healthy weight, etc.
>Why is this thread /lgbt/?
Struggles with mental and physical health are an indisputable part of /lgbt/ life, be it from dysphoria, social pressure, heartbreak, or just unfortunate lifestyle choices.
>Notes to consider:
Please be civil. Shame is your greatest enemy in fighting urges of self abuse (be it sh, drugs, or just self deprecation). Relapsing into bad and unhealthy habits is to be expected, the goal is to increase the average amount of time it takes between relapses. Any improvement is a victory no matter how small. Your worth and right to get better are non-negotiable. And most importantly:
WE ARE NOT THERAPISTS, WE DON'T REPLACE MEDICATION
>Note on advice
Generic advice won't necessarily help you in particular, but for those it does it is an essential foundation to build future progress on, not a miracle cure. Do not underestimate the effects subtle changes to your lifestyle can have. Try first, keep us posted on your progress, build from there.

We are *always* short on self help resources, so if anything was useful to you, let us know!
Since the OP is getting too long I moved all resources into their own post, see below!

I know I have the answers I need within me. I've been in a rut a long time though. I'm trying to find things that fuel me - trying to find groups and people I can bounce off, but not much luck. btw I love this thread and you're a legend for keeping it up all this time :)

I've got an ok head on my shoulders and I think I'm gonna be more or less ok. e.g. I probably won't end up in a gutter. but I am sick of just scraping along. it's just such slow progress and it does feel like I'm bearing all the burden. >>29627755
>wat kinda qotts u like?
I also preferred a lot of the old qotts
they just felt lot more specific and intentional, meaning you could get a better understanding of anons from their answers and it could create interesting discussions.
rlly broad and simple starters like "how are you feeling?" or "what's ur fav food?" end up being really hard to follow up on meaningfully, plus a lot of autists won't resonate with that stuff since it feels too superficial and flat to bother answering a lot of the time- a lot like the NT small talk that so many autists struggle to comprehend the purpose of.

I think a good strategy would be to take something broad and simple like "what's ur fav animal?" and then try to deepen that prompt by making it hyper specific. For instance, you could ask "what kind of human/animal hybrid would you wanna be?" or "what kind of mythical animal/cryptid would you like to have as a pet or familiar?" or something like that, then you can also develop other prompts off that strong base idea. It can end up being really silly or cheesy, but that's fine so long as it's something engaging for ppl to talk about. and if in doubt I would just take a step back & ask yourself "can this tap into the autistic urge to get way too in-depth about a topic?" if yes than it'll probably be good, if no then maybe tweak it a little more. At least, that;s what I think. :)

>The otokonoko page for EV says that it contains Benzyl Benzoate. I presume that it is not the same thing, right?

Benzyl benzoate is just a solvent that makes the estradiol powder dissolve faster in the vial.

You can store them anywhere that's away from sunlight and extremely hot/cold temperatures.

"Level consistency" is the same, what changes is peaks and troughs and the time between them.
